routeFacts.name: Spirit of Steam
routeFacts.description: Spirit of Steam is the first steam route for Train Sim World, featuring the route from Liverpool to Crewe set in 1958. It includes the LMS Jubilee Class and the Stanier Class 8F. DLC also features a British Guards van. For the purpose of steam locos, the HUD was redesigned and when driving a steam loco, also shows the actual reverser position in percentage. There is another HUD at the left bottom corner which shows boiler pressure, steam chest pressure and state of dampers, blower and cylinder cocks valve.
routeInfo: The route focuses on the West Coast Main Line between Crewe and Liverpool Lime Street before electrification when services were still operated by steam locomotives. The southern section of the route is a 90mph main-line from Crewe to Weaver Junction, before following the Liverpool branch of the WCML via Runcorn, where the railway crosses the Mersey on the Runcorn viaduct. Along the route there are several yards, including those at Crewe, Speke and Edge Hill.
